Competition: Campeonato Brasileiro Série A
BlockSource: http://www.rsssfbrasil.com/tablesae/br1987.htm
Season: 1987
home-first

*Originally a championship with 28 teams was to be organized by the CBF; however, Botafogo and Coritiba, who had been left out, went to a sports court and there won the right to participate.  This of course led to many other teams trying to enter the tournament.  Moreover, the CBF at the time was broke and could not finance a Brazilian championship.  This led to the breakaway of the Clube dos Treze, and two tournaments, the Copa União or Green Module and the Yellow Module organized by CBF.

*CBF also organized the dispute of the Blue and White Modules consisting of the remaining teams. Despite the press treatment of the Yellow Module as a 2nd division, and of the Blue and White Modules as a 3rd division, there was no official characterization of the four modules as divisions.

*I COPA UNIÃO/GREEN MODULE (Taça João Havelange)

*NB: this championship was organized by the "Clube dos Treze" (Club of Thirteen), independently of the Brazilian Federation (CBF).  The thirteen "big" clubs invited three others (Coritiba, Goiás and Santa Cruz-PE) and played for the Copa União.  Meanwhile the CBF organized a tournament for 16 of the clubs left out (including 1986 runners-up Guarani of Campinas), called the Yellow Module, see below, and insisted on semifinals between the top-2 of the Copa União (Flamengo and Internacional-RS) and those of the Yellow Module (Sport Recife and Guarani).  Flamengo and Internacional did not enter, and CBF inscribed Sport Recife and Guarani for the Copa Libertadores, but in 1988 the composition of the championship (called II Copa União) was based on that of the 16 teams of the Copa União 1987 (the top-7 of the Yellow Module and América-RJ were added).


*FIRST PHASE
*
*Two groups of 8 teams. In the first stage, Group A teams played against Group B teams. 
*In the second stage, teams played the other teams inside their groups. Winners of the
*groups from both stages qualified to the semifinals.
*
*First Stage
*Teams in Group A play against teams in Group B

